comments: During the rebound, Lowry (TOR) and Capela (ATL) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Boucher (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact during the play at the basket by Collins (ATL).

Lowry (TOR) has a resting hand on Young's (ATL) body and the contact is marginal during the play at the basket.  After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of offensive basket interference is overturned.

Capela (ATL) establishes himself in a screening position in Bembry's (TOR) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.  Capela absorbs the contact to his chest and midsection without delivering contact.
Boucher (TOR) places a resting hand on Young's (ATL) shoulder and marginal contact occurs that does not affect Young's SQBR.
At the start of the drive, Snell (ATL) places a resting hand to Powell's (TOR) front and the contact is marginal as it does not affect his SQBR.
Bembry (TOR) establishes himself in a screening position in Snell's (ATL) path and he firms up on his right foot to absorb the contact that is initiated by Snell.

Capela (ATL) legally contests Powell's (TOR) play at the basket and any contact to Powell's arm after the release is marginal. Powell naturally extends his leg out on the play and initiates the incidental contact with Capela's midsection.
Collins (ATL) establishes himself in a screening position in Bembry's (TOR) path and absorbs the contact from Bembry as he engages on the pick.
Boucher (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Young (ATL).
Johnson (TOR) establishes himself in a screening position in Huerter's (ATL) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.

During the rebound, Collins (ATL) and Boucher (TOR) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.  After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor that Collins touches the ball last before it bounces out of bounds is confirmed.
Snell (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact from Powell (TOR) at the end of the drive.
Upon Bembry (TOR) receiving the pass, Young (ATL) makes clean ball contact and any contact to Bembry's arm as his hand slides off is deemed marginal.
Capela (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position during the play at the basket by Bembry (TOR).
Collins (ATL) takes a straight-line path on his cut to the basket and marginal contact occurs as he engages with Bembry (TOR).
Johnson (TOR) firms up on his right foot and absorbs the contact from Young (ATL) during the drive.
